Example for crambin, pdb 9ewk.  This has a set of alternates in the
deposited structure, (unlike the 4tut example).

Basic setup:

UnitCell -p ../9ewk.pdb -o 9ewk_1uc.pdb
PropPDB -p 9ewk_1uc.pdb -o 9ewk_6uc.pdb -ix 3 -iy 2 -iz 1
./set_chainID 9ewk_6uc.pdb
make_sslinks > sslinks
./select_alts 1 9ewk_6uc.pdb > alt4.pdb

./run_alt_tleap  alt4

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
You should now be able to run cycles:

./run_cycle  0   (later 1,2,...)

A sample output from the first cycle is in alt4_001.min1.o.  Note that the
Rfactors start pretty high, but soon decrease dramatically.  Here is a
sample log file of results I got:

run_cycle  0  (200 steps PRCG)
 EAMBER  =   -27501.0011
 Exray   =   118809.1720  Rwork   =        0.1502  Rfree      =        0.1523
Start R-work = 0.1674, R-free = 0.1728
